about.summary: Collection of data sets from various assessments that can be used to evaluate psychometric models. These data sets have been analyzed in the following papers that introduced new methodology as part of the application section: Chen, Y., Culpepper, S. A., & Liang, F. (2020) <doi:10.1007/s11336-019-09693-2> Culpepper, S. A. (2019a) <doi:10.1007/s11336-019-09683-4>, Culpepper, S. A. (2019b) <doi:10.1007/s11336-018-9643-8>, Culpepper, S. A., & Chen, Y. (2019) <doi:10.3102/1076998618791306>, Culpepper, S. A., & Balamuta, J. J. (2017) <doi:10.1007/s11336-015-9484-7>, and Culpepper, S. A. (2015) <doi:10.3102/1076998615595403>.

name: r-edmdata
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.2.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-edmdata
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/edmdata_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/edmdata/edmdata_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e5e4fe4fb629e23e2f4e1e5fcde50fa6576cd593f091c5d3fa5210616dae5110

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 2
  noarch: generic

  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]

  host:
    - r-base

  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('edmdata')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('edmdata')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://tmsalab.github.io/edmdata/, https://github.com/tmsalab/edmdata/

  license: MIT
  summary: 'Collection of data sets from various assessments that can be used to evaluate psychometric models. These data sets have been analyzed in the following papers that introduced new methodology as part of the application section: Chen, Y., Culpepper, S. A., & Liang, F. (2020) <doi:10.1007/s11336-019-09693-2> Culpepper,
    S. A. (2019a) <doi:10.1007/s11336-019-09683-4>, Culpepper, S. A. (2019b) <doi:10.1007/s11336-018-9643-8>, Culpepper, S. A., & Chen, Y. (2019) <doi:10.3102/1076998618791306>, Culpepper, S. A., & Balamuta, J. J. (2017) <doi:10.1007/s11336-015-9484-7>, and Culpepper, S. A. (2015) <doi:10.3102/1076998615595403>.'

  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - coatless
    - steveculpepper
